{
  "texts": [
    "However, the computation time is rarely considered in plankton recognition literature.",
    "Most works related to the challenge consider lightweight CNN architectures.",
    "For example, shallow TANet (Li et al. 2019c) was shown to outperform competing methods in computing time without sacrificing accuracy on the Kaggle dataset.",
    "Zimmerman et al. (2020) proposed an embedded system for in situ deployment of plankton microscope with real-time recognition system.",
    "Due to the limited computation resources and computation time limitations, CNN-based recognition methods were considered unsuitable and a faster feature-engineering based approach was proposed with reduced recognition accuracy."
  ]
}